data.title: See What the Cast Gets up to Between Takes in These Candid ‘The Crown’ Photos
data.meta_description: See photos of Claire Foy, Olivia Colman, Matt Smith, Helena Bonham Carter and more stars on the royal set.
data.text:
Skip to main content

‘The Crown’ Stars Behind the Scenes Photo Gallery - Netflix Tudum

Alex Bailey/Netflix

See What the Cast Gets up to Between Takes in These Candid ‘The Crown’ Photos

Go behind the scenes in this supersized photo gallery.

Dec. 20, 2023

Even princesses need their iced coffee — at least before the camera rolls.

If you’ve just finished Season 6 — and thereby the entire series — of The Crown, why not get your royal fix with this gallery of behind-the-scenes snaps from Seasons 1 to 6 of the series. Peek inside the production process of the royal drama, which follows the reign of Queen Elizabeth II (Claire Foy, Olivia Colman and Imelda Staunton) through the years. There’s even a shot of Helena Bonham Carter (who plays Princess Margaret in Seasons 3–4), sipping on her cold brew. Who says Brits only drink tea?!

In addition to the candid photos of the stars — including Foy, Vanessa Kirby and Matt Smith (who portray Elizabeth, Margaret and Philip in Seasons 1–2) — you can also see some close-up shots of regal props, complicated setups, makeup touch-ups, costumes and more.

The Crown’s sixth season is available to stream on Netflix now.
